336
00:19:32,710 --> 00:19:36,110
-是你派我的人去的  -我吗  你在说什么
- And you sent my men. - Me? What are you talking about?

337
00:19:36,110 --> 00:19:38,280
你觉得我的人无关紧要
You saw my men as expendable.

338
00:19:39,660 --> 00:19:42,350
维克多  维和部队不归我个人管
Viktor, I don't personally oversee the peacekeeping forces,

339
00:19:42,350 --> 00:19:44,080
你不会真觉得
and you can't possibly think

340
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,580
把你的人派到危险地段
that there was some deliberate attempt

341
00:19:45,580 --> 00:19:48,350
-是有意而为的吧  -不然我该怎么想
- to put your men in harm's way. - So I am to believe, what?

342
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:51,710
这是个巧合吗
That this was a random act of fate, yes?

343
00:19:51,710 --> 00:19:53,300
听着  不管责任在谁
Listen, whoever's responsible,

344
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:56,450
我们不能让这件事离间我们的关系
we can't let them foment distrust between us.

345
00:19:56,450 --> 00:19:58,560
我们要是不和  就正中他们下怀了
If we do, then they win.

346
00:19:58,650 --> 00:20:02,030
让他们看到  意外让我们更团结
Let's show them that an incident like this makes us stronger.

347
00:20:02,030 --> 00:20:04,040
让我们帮你查出幕后黑手
Let us help you find out who did this.

348
00:20:04,050 --> 00:20:06,730
死的是俄罗斯人  俄罗斯会找出凶手
Russians are dead. Russia will find the killers.

349
00:20:06,730 --> 00:20:09,500
我不明白你为什么拒绝我们的帮助
I don't understand why you're refusing our assistance.

350
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,160
因为我们不需要
Because we don't need it.

351
00:20:11,320 --> 00:20:13,530
那我们能不能至少保持沟通
Well, can we at least keep the dialogue open?

352
00:20:13,530 --> 00:20:16,400
在进行任何行动前互相商讨一下
Consult with each other before you make any move?

353
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:20,460
我要做我必须做的  总统先生
I'm going to do what I must, Mr. President.

354
00:20:21,780 --> 00:20:23,790
维克多  请听我说  我们得
Viktor, please listen to me. We have--

355
00:20:23,790 --> 00:20:26,390
对不起  总统先生  线路挂断了
I'm sorry, Mr. President, but the line has been disconnected.

356
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,980
他挂我电话
He hung up on me.

357
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,880
帮我接凯茜·杜兰特
Cathy Durant, please.

358
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,290
鲍德温说得没错
Baldwin was right.

359
00:20:43,330 --> 00:20:45,810
死去的八名战士给了佩特罗夫一个借口
Those eight bodies give Petrov options.

360
00:20:45,810 --> 00:20:49,680
他才没有潸然泪下  他在开香槟庆祝呢
He's not shedding tears, he's popping champagne corks.

361
00:20:49,950 --> 00:20:51,260
我能听到
I can hear them.

362
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:07,860
不在这儿  先生  卫生间在这边
Not here. Sir. Restroom's this way.

363
00:21:09,340 --> 00:21:12,150
刚那是谁  刚进来的那人是谁
Who was that? The guy who just came in?

364
00:21:12,430 --> 00:21:13,380
没看到
Didn't see him.

365
00:23:32,060 --> 00:23:33,880
我可以到你办公室去
I would've come to your office.

366
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:37,110
这是联合国唯一一间俄国没有监控的房间
This is the only room at the UN we don't monitor.

367
00:23:37,210 --> 00:23:41,390
-我想你们也没有监控  -没  美国也没有
- I'm assuming you don't either. - No, we haven't bugged it.

368
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:45,130
-那我们能打开天窗说亮话了  -也该说了
- So we can speak openly. - I think we should.

369
00:23:48,910 --> 00:23:51,590
你说  我听着
You talk. I'll listen.

370
00:23:55,030 --> 00:23:56,570
巴勒斯坦说如果以色列军队进入河谷
Palestine says it can't control Hamas

371
00:23:56,570 --> 00:23:58,990
他们控制不了哈马斯
if Israeli troops cross into the valley.

372
00:24:00,840 --> 00:24:02,470
我们只能私下沟通  亚历克西
We have to back channel this, Alexi.

373
00:24:02,470 --> 00:24:05,120
佩特罗夫不肯听弗兰西斯的
Petrov won't listen to Francis.

374
00:24:11,550 --> 00:24:14,880
亚历克西  这事你不能坐视不管
Alexi, please. This whole thing, you can't let it devolve

375
00:24:14,880 --> 00:24:17,250
让事态完全失控
into something nobody can control.

376
00:24:17,850 --> 00:24:19,930
也许这就是目的所在
Well, maybe that was the objective.

377
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:22,740
什么目的
What was?

378
00:24:25,060 --> 00:24:29,070
总统本来就反对这次维和任务
The President... never wanted the peacekeeping mission.

379
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:30,330
你刚说"目的"
You said "Objective."

380
00:24:30,330 --> 00:24:32,350
你是说这都是计划好的吗
Are you telling me this was somehow planned?

381
00:24:32,350 --> 00:24:34,050
我什么都没说
I haven't said anything.

382
00:24:35,530 --> 00:24:36,900
但你想说
But you want to.

383
00:24:37,370 --> 00:24:40,180
全世界都想知道这件事是谁干的
The whole world wants to know who is responsible.

384
00:24:40,290 --> 00:24:42,990
你们的军队不让任何人进入爆炸地点
Your troops won't let anyone near the blast site.

385
00:24:48,950 --> 00:24:51,050
因为他们不想让世人知道真相
Because they don't want the world to know.

386
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:54,250
我弟弟  他在俄罗斯联邦安全局
My brother... he's in the FSB.

387
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:58,560
我们一周前还说过话  那之后就没了音讯
We spoke a week ago. I haven't heard from him since.

388
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:01,920
你万分确定吗
Are you absolutely certain about this?

389
00:25:05,210 --> 00:25:06,800
亚历克西  公开吧
Alexi, go public.

390
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,070
我们会庇护你的
We'll protect you.

391
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,000
就像你们庇护冯山德那样吗
Like you did Xander Feng?

392
00:25:14,610 --> 00:25:15,770
这是两码事
That was different.

393
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:18,840
我还有家庭
I have a family.

394
00:25:21,620 --> 00:25:24,490
俄联邦安全局以前也干过这种事
The FSB has conducted these sorts of operations before.

395
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:26,280
公寓被炸事件
The apartment complex that blew up,

396
00:25:24,500 --> 00:25:29,330
{\pos(382,284)}{\an3}1999年9月
莫斯科等城市发生多起公寓被炸案
俄罗斯指责是车臣叛军所为
车臣叛军则指控是俄秘密部门所为

397
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:29,330
成了佩特罗夫用来进攻车臣的理由
Petrov used that to justify invading Chechnya.

398
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:31,530
剧院毒气事件
The opera house that was gassed,

399
00:25:29,660 --> 00:25:33,800
{\pos(382,284)}{\an3}2002年10月23至26日
俄突击队冲入莫斯科一家戏院
营救被车臣叛军扣压的七百名俄国人质
最终129名人质死亡
41名车臣叛军被击毙
多数人死于未知毒气

400
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,800
那之后他换掉了所有省长
he removed all provincial governors after that.

401
00:25:33,800 --> 00:25:36,830
我们的确认为第一件事与俄联邦安全局有关
We do believe the FSB participated in the first.

402
00:25:36,830 --> 00:25:39,370
剧院事件我们仍不确定
We're still uncertain about the opera house.

403
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,540
但炸死他自己的士兵
But blowing up his own soldiers,

404
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,500
我还是觉得难以置信
I find that very difficult to believe.

405
00:25:43,500 --> 00:25:47,690
他直截了当地说了吗  他说出口了吗
Did he tell you point blank? Did he say the words?

406
00:25:48,660 --> 00:25:50,670
他把能说的都说了
He said as much as he could.

407
00:25:50,860 --> 00:25:53,030
但他的暗示很明确
But the implication was crystal clear.

408
00:25:53,030 --> 00:25:54,850
我相信他一定很令人信服
I'm sure he was very convincing.

409
00:25:54,850 --> 00:25:56,210
俄国所有外交官都经过了
All Russian diplomats go through

410
00:25:56,210 --> 00:25:57,940
俄联邦安全局的反情报训练
FSB counter-intel training.

411
00:25:57,940 --> 00:26:00,750
他们想刺激我们做出行动
They're trying to provoke some sort of reaction out of us.

412
00:26:01,000 --> 00:26:02,140
那他弟弟呢
But what about his brother?

413
00:26:02,140 --> 00:26:04,680
他弟弟确实是在俄联邦安全局工作
It is true that his brother works for the FSB,

414
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,470
我们也的确上周后就找不到他了
and that we lost track of him last week.

415
00:26:06,480 --> 00:26:07,950
这部分属实
That part of the story holds up.

416
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,620
我们对莫里科夫有什么了解
What's our profile on Moryakov?

417
00:26:09,620 --> 00:26:12,320
我们有特工调查过他  先生  吉姆
We have our agent who's been assigned to him, sir. Jim?

418
00:26:12,320 --> 00:26:16,050
莫斯科认为莫里科夫有点捉摸不定
Moryakov has been considered a bit of a wild card in Moscow.

419
00:26:16,050 --> 00:26:18,110
佩特罗夫曾两次考虑将他召回
Petrov considered recalling him twice,

420
00:26:18,110 --> 00:26:20,660
但碍于和他父亲的交情就不了了之
but held off because his father's a family friend.

421
00:26:20,670 --> 00:26:23,160
这几个月来我们收集到些只言片语
Now, we picked up some chatter in recent months,

422
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:26,840
他对克林姆林宫处理约旦河谷问题的方式有所担忧
his misgivings with how the Kremlin's been handling the Jordan Valley.

423
00:26:27,430 --> 00:26:29,920
但你觉得他会做叛徒吗
But does he strike you as a traitor?

424
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:32,660
他很难说  他极度民族主义
He's a complicated man. Fiercely nationalistic.

425
00:26:32,660 --> 00:26:35,860
但他对佩特罗夫绝对有疑虑
But he definitely has doubts about Petrov.

426
00:26:39,990 --> 00:26:42,140
我们至少该考虑一下这种可能吧
Shouldn't we at least entertain the possibility?

427
00:26:42,140 --> 00:26:43,380
是啊  但我们怎么确定
Yeah, but how can we determine it

428
00:26:43,380 --> 00:26:45,420
到底是怎么样的  如何确认
one way or the other? Definitively?

429
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,920
光靠卫星不够
Our satellites aren't enough.

430
00:26:46,930 --> 00:26:48,480
我们得派人去爆炸地点
We'd have to get men to the blast site,

431
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:51,480
采集土壤样本和爆炸残片
retrieve soil samples and blast debris.

432
00:26:52,690 --> 00:26:54,600
我们多快能派人过去
How soon could we get a team in?

433
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:56,610
72小时吧
I'd estimate 72 hours.

434
00:26:56,740 --> 00:26:58,610
三天也太久了
Well, three days seems an awfully long time.

435
00:26:58,610 --> 00:27:01,340
调派的基本准备不是已经就绪了吗
Don't we already have the basics in place for deployment?

436
00:27:01,340 --> 00:27:03,660
但那没有考虑应对俄罗斯军队
That doesn't take into account the Russian forces.

437
00:27:03,660 --> 00:27:05,910
我们想在出兵之前掌握更多情报
We'd want better intel before deploying.

438
00:27:09,570 --> 00:27:12,340
那是不是随着时间推移
Am I correct in assuming that every hour that passes,

439
00:27:12,340 --> 00:27:15,450
我们获取证据的几率也在降低
our chances of retrieving any proof diminish?

440
00:27:15,880 --> 00:27:17,260
是的  先生
That is correct, sir.

441
00:27:17,430 --> 00:27:20,270
那调派最快需要多久
What's the absolute soonest you can deploy?

442
00:27:21,720 --> 00:27:23,340
12小时  总统先生
Twelve hours, Mr. President.

443
00:27:23,340 --> 00:27:25,320
但这样就有极高的...
But that would involve an extremely high degree--

444
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:27,580
我知道有风险  上将
Yeah, I'm aware of the risk, Admiral.

445
00:27:28,030 --> 00:27:29,880
胜算有多大
What are the odds of success?

446
00:27:31,030 --> 00:27:33,930
说实话  先生  没有准确情报
Honestly, sir, without proper intelligence,

447
00:27:34,690 --> 00:27:36,590
我最多只能说一半一半
I can't say better than 50/50.

448
00:27:38,860 --> 00:27:40,040
你确定吗
You're certain?

449
00:27:41,090 --> 00:27:42,750
我确定
Yes, I am.

450
00:27:47,080 --> 00:27:48,310
那就准备行动
Let's put it in motion.

451
00:27:51,130 --> 00:27:53,420
-总统先生  -马克
- Mr. President? - Mark.

452
00:27:53,430 --> 00:27:55,570
不是应该联合国去调查
Shouldn't the UN be conducting the investigation

453
00:27:55,570 --> 00:27:56,480
而不是俄罗斯吗
instead of the Russians?

454
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:57,850
俄罗斯在此次行动之初
The Russians have been our partners

455
00:27:57,850 --> 00:27:59,710
就是我们的合作伙伴
in this mission from day one of deployment,

456
00:27:59,710 --> 00:28:03,820
所以我认为他们是代表联合国进行自主调查
so I would say that they're conducting their own investigation on behalf

457
00:28:03,990 --> 00:28:06,900
而不是取代联合国
of the United Nations, not instead of.

458
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:08,940
-总统先生  -萨拉
- Mr. President? - Sara.

459
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:09,760
那是不是说
Is it correct to say that

460
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:11,820
他们不会向联合国指挥部汇报
they are in no way reporting to UN Command?

461
00:28:11,820 --> 00:28:14,790
在维和任务中  每个国家志愿派遣军力
In peacekeeping missions, nations volunteer their forces.

462
00:28:14,790 --> 00:28:16,910
他们首先是听命于本国政府
They answer to their own governments first and foremost,

463
00:28:16,910 --> 00:28:18,800
其次再是与联合国指挥部合作
then they cooperate with the UN Command.

464
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,350
两者有重要区别
That's an important distinction to make.

465
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:23,410
其他关于约旦河谷的问题
Now, any other questions with respect to the Jordan Valley

466
00:28:23,410 --> 00:28:24,930
都请向国务院提出
should be directed to the State Department.

467
00:28:24,930 --> 00:28:25,980
如果还有跟昨天的事
But if any of you have questions

468
00:28:25,980 --> 00:28:27,770
无关的问题
that don't relate to yesterday's events,

469
00:28:27,770 --> 00:28:30,210
我可以回答一下  斯黛芬妮
I'll take one or two. Yeah, Stephanie.

470
00:28:30,220 --> 00:28:32,700
总统先生  我跟凯特都有个问题
Mr. President, Kate and I both had a question.

471
00:28:32,840 --> 00:28:33,760
谢谢  斯黛芬妮
Thank you, Stephanie.

472
00:28:33,770 --> 00:28:34,980
总统先生  您知道
Mr. President, are you aware, sir,

473
00:28:34,980 --> 00:28:36,600
在空军一号上进行竞选活动
that campaigning on Air Force One

474
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:39,560
-是违反选举委员会规定的吗  -我知道
- is a violation of FEC rules? - Yes, in general, I am.

475
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:41,680
昨天哈兰·特劳伯也在飞机上
Harlan Traub was on the plane yesterday.

476
00:28:41,680 --> 00:28:42,850
他出现在那儿的原因
It's hard to imagine he was there

477
00:28:42,850 --> 00:28:45,290
大概只能是你在寻求他在爱荷华州的支持吧
for any other reason than you'd be seeking his support in Iowa.

478
00:28:45,290 --> 00:28:46,710
你不知道  我跟他是老交情了
You don't know how long I've known him,

479
00:28:46,710 --> 00:28:48,410
他昨天的确在飞机上
and yes, he was on the plane yesterday.

480
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:51,350
但我没进行选举活动就不算违规
But it's not a violation if you don't campaign, which I didn't.

481
00:28:51,350 --> 00:28:53,210
我也就问了问
I think the extent of our conversation

482
00:28:53,210 --> 00:28:54,850
他吃得怎么样
was asking him how he liked his meal.

483
00:28:54,850 --> 00:28:57,330
不过我乐意接受选举委员会的裁决
But I'm happy to let the FEC decide.

484
00:28:57,330 --> 00:28:58,980
还有谁要受人所托
Now, does anybody else have any question

485
00:28:58,980 --> 00:29:00,850
问我什么问题吗
that somebody else asked them to ask me?

486
00:29:01,910 --> 00:29:02,910
特劳伯呢
Where's Traub now?

487
00:29:02,910 --> 00:29:05,030
酒店里  一小时内能到
At the Hay-Adams. Should be here in an hour.

488
00:29:05,030 --> 00:29:07,080
被人看见他在白宫不好吧
It'd be bad if anyone saw him at the White House.

489
00:29:07,080 --> 00:29:08,700
我现在都不想让他来首都
Well, I don't even want him in DC now.

490
00:29:08,700 --> 00:29:11,250
我得处理俄罗斯的问题
The last thing we need is some bullshit FEC story

491
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:12,850
不能再让选举委员会找上茬
while I'm trying to deal with the Russians.

492
00:29:12,850 --> 00:29:14,840
送他回爱荷华吧  你来处理
Let's get him back to Iowa. And you handle this.

493
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,650
你比沃恩更擅长与人打交道
You have better people skills than Vaughn.

494
00:29:16,650 --> 00:29:17,570
你跟鲍德温谈
And you talk to Baldwin.

495
00:29:17,570 --> 00:29:20,380
跟她说明白我们没违反任何规定
You make it crystal clear we violated no regulations.

496
00:29:20,380 --> 00:29:23,640
先生  道格昨晚给我留言了
Sir? I got a voicemail from Doug last night.

497
00:29:23,650 --> 00:29:27,560
-他说他母亲去世了  -真糟糕
- He said his mom died. - My God, that's awful.

498
00:29:28,190 --> 00:29:30,440
可是茱莉亚·斯坦普十年前就去世了
Except Julia Stamper passed away ten years ago.

499
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:32,400
我知道  我去了葬礼
I know, I was at the funeral.

500
00:29:32,870 --> 00:29:35,000
送些花吧  把道格请来吧
Send some flowers. Actually, get Doug in here.

501
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,460
我想亲自表示哀悼
I'd like to give my condolences in person.

502
00:29:40,140 --> 00:29:41,020
通过《美国就业法案》
There's a whole host of ways

503
00:29:41,020 --> 00:29:42,990
